  "summary": "After Mukai confronts Kanou regarding his concern for his daughter, Kaneko is shocked when Mukai mentions Mizuho, a topic not previously discussed. Sugata (Muto) reveals his motive for the visit, explaining that he intended to claim Mizuho but was prevented by the death of her mother, Maria Kuchera, a foreigner he met in America. This revelation implies that Mizuho is of mixed race, a fact that would have faced intense opposition from the xenophobic Kagura family and the Kishijiro bloodline.\n\nBecause Sugata feels unable to protect Mizuho himself due to family opposition, he asks Shizu to take on the responsibility. Although Shizu suggests Tsukimi might be a better candidate, Sugata reluctantly agrees to protect Mizuho while he travels to investigate the case. Following Kaneko's departure, the group discusses the assignment. Mutsuji performs string tricks while playing \"Death and the Maiden\" on an amplifier.\n\nThe conversation shifts toward the nature of the investigation and the identity of the killer. The group speculates on the motives of Kaname, suggesting he may have been torn between his inheritance and his mistress. Mukutsumi proposes a theory that the killer could be the mistress, implying the situation could have turned deadly if she discovered Kaname's true intentions. The passage concludes as Hina announces dinner time, and the narrator notes that Kumozawa has been missing since 10:00 AM.",
